Speed / Relative Speed
Two trains 120 m and 180 m long are moving in opposite directions with speeds 54 km/h and 36 km/h respectively. How long will they take to cross each other?

Profit & Loss (Calendar profit twist)
A trader marks up his goods by 25% on cost price and allows two successive discounts of 10% each on the marked price. What is his approximate profit or loss percentage?

Combinatorics
From 8 men and 7 women, in how many ways can a committee of 4 people be formed such that it contains at least 2 women?

Probability (Conditional style)
Two cards are drawn one after another without replacement from a standard deck of 52 cards. What is the probability that both are Aces?

Geometry (Circle / chord)
A chord of a circle is 10 cm long and is at a distance 6 cm from the center. Find the radius of the circle.

Time & Work (With leak)
A cistern can be filled by a pipe in 8 hours. Due to a leak, it actually takes 10 hours to fill. How long would the leak alone take to empty a full cistern?

